values:
Hello people. 

It has been a while since my last journal entry, so I guess I'd better start by wishing everyone a merry christmas & a happy new year! 

Christmas was good, new years was good, my birthday was good... 
At this point in my life I'm actually pretty happy. However I feel a need to quote my friend Aleks because that is pretty much the only thing that I really want, that & a new job ;D:
"I just want someone to snuggle up with in a couch, just watching some horrible christmas movie or something. I don't want the hottest girl, just a cutie to snuggle with."
However, it doesn't even have to be a horrible christmas movie for me. ;) 
Anyways, it has happened wuite a bit since my last entry: 
First & foremost my birthday was december 30th. so I am now 19!! God, this is a fucking meaningless age, nothing happens at this age.. I mean in Sweden when you become 18 you can go into most bars, atleast on fridays, you can take your drivers license. When you become 20 you can shop liquor at "systembolaget" that is the only place in Sweden where you can shop liquor legally. 

Gah, I can't be arsed to tell you about what I have done to be honest... 

It's early 2007 & I have discovered stress... 

Laters!!!!

Hello there boys & girls that might read this journal - probably noone bu whatever.
Ok, so let's start with one bad thing that I feel a need to write about. You know that job I was applying for? Well, I didn't get it & I feel fucking worthless right now. 

I got home from Stockholm yesterday & I had a fucking blast, especially at the concert but it was really nice seing Aleksander again - he's a terrific guy. ^^ Red Hot Chili Peppers blew me away, I loved the whole experience everything except John's solo-thing with his kind of a gay pop-song but it was pretty cool anyways. The only thing that wasn't good with Stockholm was that I felt this huge guilt for lying to one of my dearest friends & my ex. girlfriend Paulina. 
Here's the deal:
Her last week was really rough & she was vulnerable and because I still have feelings for her I didn't think it would be a good idea if we met up in Stockholm because if something happened and we would end up together I don't think it would be a very good thing because of the fact that she lives 500 kilometres from me & that can really suck. And if we got back together I don't really think it would be for the right reasons, more of a reboud thing, you know? 
So, I lied to her & said I was going to Germany with some friends instead of what I was actually going to do because of the reasons I just gave you. And now I feel like a fucking ass! I feel so bad because I hate to lie to people I love 6 now I don't know what to do, if I'm gonna let her recover or if I'm gonna just tell her now. 

Drive safe, everybody... Laters.

What cookin', gang? I know, a really corny opener but I've always wanted to say that for some reason. Maybe It's the same reason that I feel that I need to say "Guvna'" after each sentence if I'm talking to a person from Great Britain...

Anyways, this is my first post... 
Today has been kind of a good day, the only things I have done today is sleeping & watching South Park. 
Worked pretty much all weekend  plus yesterday, so that sucked big time but I got today off so I guess it's ok. I'm a waiter with a crappy salary so I'm not all that excited to go to work tomorrow either. 

Got to thinking again, yesterday and that kind of got me down. Had a discussion with my mother a couple of days ago & somehow we started talking about things that me & my brothers teachers had said about us over the years & they all said pretty much the same thing: "They have alot of potential but they dont use any of it." So I started thinking about what I could have done if I had paid attention in school instead of slacking around the way I did. Maybe I would have been doing something completely different & maybe I had been happy. Pretty wierd to think about that, you know?

Anyways, I'm really looking forward to this sunday. I'm going up to the capitol of Sweden - Stockholm - to see my good friend Aleksander & we are going to go see a concert with one of my favourite bands of all times: Red Hot Chili Peppers. 
Oh well, I have to get going... Going to meet up with a friend downtown and we're gonna have some dinner or whatever. 
Anyhow, good talking to you even if noone is ever gonna read this shit. Haha.

Laters. 

/Samuel
